This seminar is designed to teach the doctoral students the key points that should exist in a publishable academic paper and to develop the critical thinking skills of these students. The students will learn what to do and what to avoid when writing papers and what the requirements are for mature papers. Doctoral students are expected to give a critical review of the paper(s) at the seminar and to present their views.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to develop the analytical skills of graduate students and train them to work with literature.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing this course:  The student develops critical thinking when they read academic papers  The student knows the key aspects of writing publishable academic papers  The student learns how to write referee reports The student improves presentation skills
